et: Middle English {it}wodebinde{/it}, from Old English {it}wudubinde{/it}, from {it}wudu{/it} wood + {it}bindan{/it} to tie, bind; from its winding around trees
shortdef: any of several honeysuckles; especially : a Eurasian twining shrub (Lonicera periclymenum)

dt: {bc}a common North American tendril-climbing vine ({it}Parthenocissus quinquefolia{/it}) of the grape family with palmately compound leaves and bluish-black berries

shortdef: a common North American tendril-climbing vine (Parthenocissus quinquefolia) of the grape family with palmately compound leaves and bluish-black berries —called also woodbine
